+/* SROM revision 11 — offsets verified by direct cross-reference of the
+ * raw `wl srdump` output against the nominal `wl nvram_dump` output of
+ * a BCM4352-family board (DSL-3580L). Each definition below is the
+ * unique byte offset at which the named field is observed in the SROM.
+ *
+ * Fields whose SROM value is zero on the reference board (because the
+ * board profile does not exercise that band/rate) cannot be located by
+ * value-match alone; for those — listed at the end of this block as a
+ * comment — the offset proposal below is the position derived from the
+ * struct ssb_sprom declaration order, which the bcm47xx_sprom NVRAM
+ * fallback path also follows. Cross-board confirmation pending; see
+ * sprom-rev11/README.md.
+ */
+/* Rev-11 header offsets that DO NOT match the rev-8 layout. Three
+ * fields shifted past their rev-8 positions on the BCM4352 reference
+ * board: IL0MAC by 4 bytes (rev-8 0x8C, rev-11 0x90), ANTAVAIL by 4
+ * bytes (0x9C -> 0xA0), TXRXC by 6 bytes (0xA2 -> 0xA8). The bitfield
+ * masks (SSB_SPROM8_ANTAVAIL_A/_BG, SSB_SPROM8_TXRXC_TXCHAIN/_RXCHAIN/
+ * _SWITCH) are reused unchanged: only the absolute offset moved, the
+ * field layout within each word is the same. boardrev (0x82) does
+ * coincide between rev 8 and rev 11 and continues to be read from
+ * SSB_SPROM8_BOARDREV.
+ */
+#define SSB_SPROM11_IL0MAC		0x0090
+#define SSB_SPROM11_ANTAVAIL		0x00A0
+#define SSB_SPROM11_TXRXC		0x00A8
